# Date versioning for releases and artifacts

Follow **date-based versioning** for the main AnimeDB app. See `docs/adr/2026-03-02-date-versioning-for-releases-and-artifacts.md` for the full ADR.

## Main app

- **Git release tags:** `vYYYY.MM.DD` for the first release of the day (e.g. `v2026.03.03`). For **multiple releases the same day**, use `vYYYY.MM.DD.N` with N = 2, 3, … (e.g. `v2026.03.03.2`). First of the day = no suffix; second = `.2`, third = `.3`, etc.
- **CHANGELOG section headings:** `[YYYY-MM-DD]` (e.g. `[2026-03-02]`). One section per release or one per day with multiple entries as needed.
- **Artifacts:** Name or reference artifacts with the same version as the release (the tag) they belong to.

## Install script

- **Filenames:** `install_v<N>.ps1` with N an integer incremented each release (e.g. `install_v39.ps1`). Not tied to the calendar date; used for cache-busting. See `.cursorrules` for the commit checklist (copy `install.ps1` → new `install_v<N>.ps1`, remove old, update README).

## Sub-projects (e.g. UPnP Tray)

- **Date versioning:** Tray uses the same date scheme. Release tag: `upnp-tray-vYYYY.MM.DD`. The setup exe is built with the date in the name (e.g. `AnimeDB UPnP Setup 2026.3.6.exe`). The release script sets `package.json` version to the date before building. Both releases must have the **setup exe and latest.yml** attached. **latest.yml path/url must match the actual exe filename:** electron-builder may write dashed names in latest.yml (`AnimeDB-UPnP-Setup-*.exe`) while the NSIS exe has spaces (`AnimeDB UPnP Setup *.exe`). The release script patches latest.yml before upload so the in-app updater can download the file; keep this behavior when changing the release flow.

## When creating or updating releases

Follow the **Release process** in `.cursorrules`. Steps:

1. **Version and changelog:** Use today’s date or the next calendar date. Update CHANGELOG under `[YYYY-MM-DD]`. Install script: new `install_v<N>.ps1`, remove old, update README. Tray version is set by the release script to the date.
2. **Commit and push** all release-related changes.
3. **Build and publish:** Run `.\scripts\release.ps1` (optionally `-Date "YYYY-MM-DD"`). The script builds the UPnP Tray and creates both releases, attaching the setup exe and latest.yml to each. Use `$env:CI = $null` if the tray build fails on publish.
4. **Verify** both releases have the setup exe and latest.yml attached; commit and push any post-release changes. See `.cursorrules` for the full Release process.
